ng effects and associated\npoloidal drift of the blob that was observed in the 3D simulations.\n  Although the sheath dissipation closure was concluded to be more successful\nin replicating the 3D dynamics, it is emphasised that the vorticity closure may\nstill be relevant for situations where the parallel current is inhibited from\nclosing through the sheath due to effects such as increased resistivity near\nthe targets.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 8 Oct 2014 14:32:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-23"}
